… Partnership to Support 245 MSMEs, 440 Jobs First City Monument Bank (FCMB) in collaboration with the French Development Agency (AFD) has signed a deal that supports FCMB provision of N4bn worth of loan to Nigeria’s Medium and Small Scale Enterprises (MSMEs). The agreement was made possible by both parties signing of a N2bn risk-sharing facility.
Aimed at providing access to appropriate sources of funding for MSMEs which represents 96 per cent of all businesses in Nigeria. The deal is estimated to support close to 245 Nigerian MSMEs, in addition to creating and sustaining 440 jobs. This move is both parties’ acknowledgement of the critical role of the sector in Nigeria’s economy. It is also the second partnership between FCMB, one of Nigeria’s top ten banks, and Proparco, AFD’s private sector financing arm, which has ben dedicated to the promotion of sustainable economic, social and environmental development practices for the past 40 years. The first partnership took place in 2012 where Proparco granted a $2.5m loan to FCMB to support the latter’s lending activity to the infrastructure sector. It is also part of AFD’s 2019 initiative Choose Africa which has dedicated €2.5bn to accelerating the growth of MSMEs in Africa by 2022.